Package: icetea
Title: R package for processing and analysis of CAGE data
Version: 0.98.0
Authors@R: person("Vivek", "Bhardwaj", email = "bhardwaj@ie-freiburg.mpg.de", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: icetea is a tool for processing and analysis of CAGE data, from raw reads to TSS calling and differential TSS detection.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.3)
Imports:
    stats, utils, methods, graphics, grDevices,
    plyr, reshape2, ggplot2, GenomicFeatures, ShortRead,
    BiocParallel, Biostrings, S4Vectors, Rsamtools, BiocGenerics, IRanges,
    GenomicAlignments, GenomicRanges, rtracklayer, SummarizedExperiment,
    VariantAnnotation, limma, edgeR, csaw, Rsubread
biocViews: Transcription, GeneExpression, Sequencing, RNASeq, Transcriptomics,
            DifferentialExpression, Annotation, SequencingData, ExpressionData
URL: https://github.com/vivekbhr/icetea
License: GPL-3
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
Suggests: knitr,
    rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
